<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF9BFF89FF7EF97BFB43FEA8" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="270" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9BFF88FF7EF97BFD05F808" blockId="26.[136,1452,1710,2061]" pageId="26" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9BFF88FF7EF97BFEE5F928" bold="true" box="[136,274,1710,1736]" pageId="26" pageNumber="269">Description</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF9BFF88FEA9F97BFDE2F929" author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[351,533,1710,1737]" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" refId="ref33002" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2008) Water starworts of Europe. BSBI Handbook No. 11. Botanical Society of the British Isles, London, UK. 180 pp." type="book" year="2008">Lansdown 2008</bibRefCitation>
):—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves ± parallelsided or tapering from base, often sinuous, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FD80F907FCECF90D" box="[630,795,1746,1773]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9449999999999998" metricValueMax="2.85" metricValueMin="1.04" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="19.45" valueMax="28.5" valueMin="10.4">10.4–28.5 mm</quantity>
long × 0.1–2. mm wide; expanded submerged or floating leaves elongate-spathulate to elliptic, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FDCFF923FD29F8F1" box="[569,734,1782,1809]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.59" metricValueMin="1.1099999999999999" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.9" valueMin="11.1">11.1–15.9 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FCCAF922FC46F8F1" box="[828,945,1783,1809]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="2.9" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="2.0">2–3.8 mm</quantity>
wide, 3-veined often with one or two short processes arising from the secondary veins; petiole (0.3–) 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FCF2F8CFFC7DF8D5" box="[772,906,1818,1845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="3.3" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="1.1">1.1–5.5 mm</quantity>
long; the apical leaves forming a floating rosette; leaves of terrestrial plants 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FE49F8EBFDBEF8B9" box="[447,585,1854,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3.8 mm</quantity>
long × 0.5–1.8(–2.3) mm wide, narrowly elliptic. Flowers solitary. Bracts translucent, appearing whitish, falcate, persistent 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FD58F8B7FCC3F89D" box="[686,820,1890,1917]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–2.6 mm</quantity>
long. Styles erect and slightly curved, 0.5–6.5(–7.8) mm long. Filament initially erect, ultimately recurved ≤ 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FD22F852FCDBF841" box="[724,812,1927,1953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="8.3">8.3 mm</quantity>
long; anthers (0.5–) 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FBF9F853FB6DF841" box="[1039,1178,1926,1953]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.8 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FB05F853FA91F841" box="[1267,1382,1926,1953]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="0.8" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.6">0.6–1 mm</quantity>
wide, quadrilocular; pollen yellow. Fruit not strumose, subsessile, ± as wide as high, pale brown when mature, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FAD2F87EFA5BF825" box="[1316,1452,1963,1989]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.7 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FF2EF81AFEA8F809" box="[216,351,1999,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.8 mm</quantity>
wide, narrowly winged throughout.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9BFF88FF4BF827FC13F7EC" blockId="26.[136,1452,1710,2061]" box="[189,996,2034,2061]" pageId="26" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9BFF88FF4BF827FEAEF7EC" bold="true" box="[189,345,2034,2060]" pageId="26" pageNumber="269">Illustrations:</emphasis>
—Figures on pages 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9BFF88FDCCF827FD40F7EC" box="[570,695,2034,2061]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9082999999999997" metricValueMax="2.921" metricValueMin="2.8956" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" unit="in" value="114.5" valueMax="115.0" valueMin="114.0">114–115 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF9BFF88FD4BF827FC82F7ED" author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[701,885,2034,2061]" pageId="26" pageNumber="269" refId="ref33002" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2008) Water starworts of Europe. BSBI Handbook No. 11. Botanical Society of the British Isles, London, UK. 180 pp." type="book" year="2008">Lansdown 2008</bibRefCitation>
. 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF9BFF88FC89F827FC17F7EC" box="[895,992,2034,2060]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,190,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-15@17.[151,1436,190,1889]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. heterophylla, b—C. insularis, c—C. muelleri, d—C. palustris, e—C. papuana, f—C. peploides, g—C. petriei, h—C. platycarpa, i—C. sonderi, j—C. stagnalis, k—C. umbonata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577553/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="269">Fig. 10h</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9AFF89FF4BFF4BFB43FEA8" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FF4BFF4BFEA1FF58" bold="true" box="[189,342,158,184]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FE84FF4AFDFDFF58" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1831" box="[370,522,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FE84FF4AFDFDFF58" box="[370,522,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. platycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FC85FF4BFBB4FF58" box="[883,1091,158,184]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FC85FF4BFC1BFF58" box="[883,1004,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region except 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FAD1FF4AFA5CFF58" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[1319,1451,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FAD1FF4AFA5CFF58" box="[1319,1451,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the large, winged, pale brownish-grey fruit. It can only reliably be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FB98FF16FB03FF3C" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[1134,1268,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FB98FF16FB03FF3C" box="[1134,1268,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pollen of which most in each anther is bluntly triangular, as opposed to ellipsoid in 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FC3BFF32FBA4FEE0" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[973,1107,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FC3BFF32FBA4FEE0" box="[973,1107,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FB94FF32FB0AFEE0" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1831" box="[1122,1277,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FB94FF32FB0AFEE0" box="[1122,1277,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. platycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
often produces linear, submerged leaves which are very rare in 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FD49FEDEFCBEFEC4" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[703,841,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FD49FEDEFCBEFEC4" box="[703,841,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the fruit of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FBD9FEDEFB3BFEC4" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1831" box="[1071,1228,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FBD9FEDEFB3BFEC4" box="[1071,1228,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. platycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are typically more narrowly-winged than in 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FE52FEFAFDDDFEA8" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[420,554,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FE52FEFAFDDDFEA8" box="[420,554,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and more greyish, but these characters are not diagnostic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF9AFF89FF4BFE87FB6DFCFC" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9AFF89FF4BFE87FB80FE54" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FF4BFE87FEAEFE8C" bold="true" box="[189,345,338,364]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Non-native. Within the region. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FD17FE87FC2AFE8C" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1831" box="[737,989,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FD17FE87FC2AFE8C" box="[737,989,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Callitriche platycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported from a single site in 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF9AFF89FF7EFEA2FED4FE70" box="[136,291,374,401]" name="New Zealand" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. In its native range it is mainly found in western Europe. It occurs throughout Britain and 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF9AFF89FADDFEA3FA8DFE70" box="[1323,1402,374,400]" name="Ireland" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Ireland</collectingCountry>
and throughout 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF9AFF89FEFCFE4EFEAEFE55" box="[266,345,411,437]" name="France" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">France</collectingCountry>
, extending north into southern 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF9AFF89FD40FE4FFCF8FE54" box="[694,783,410,436]" name="Sweden" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Sweden</collectingCountry>
and east to the 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF9AFF89FC4BFE4FFB84FE54" box="[957,1139,410,436]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9AFF89FF4BFE6BFBCDFDC0" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FF4BFE6BFE32FE38" bold="true" box="[189,453,446,472]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<location id="DA0539ADFF9AFF89FE17FE6BFDD5FE38" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:5773DE60FF9BFF89FF7EF9CBFB6DFCFC:DA0539ADFF9AFF89FE17FE6BFDD5FE38" box="[481,546,446,472]" country="New Zealand" municipality="In" name="There" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">There</location>
is no information on the habitat in which it was reported from 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF9AFF89FB24FE6AFA9CFE38" box="[1234,1387,446,473]" name="New Zealand" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="3F01F50CFF9AFF89FA82FE6AFA7CFE39" box="[1396,1419,447,473]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">In</collectingMunicipality>
its native range 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FEECFE37FDE2FE1C" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1831" box="[282,533,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FEECFE37FDE2FE1C" box="[282,533,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Callitriche platycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically occurs in lowland ditches, canals, streams, ponds and river backwaters. 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9AFF89FF7EFDD3FF1CFDC1" box="[136,235,518,545]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="260.0" valueMax="520.0" valueMin="0.0">
<elevation id="54F78845FF9AFF89FF7EFDD3FF1CFDC1" box="[136,235,518,545]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="260.0" valueMax="520.0" valueMin="0.0">0–520 m</elevation>
</quantity>
elevation in its native range, Palmerston North is at around 
<quantity id="1822C293FF9AFF89FC7AFDD3FC32FDC1" box="[908,965,518,545]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="50.0">
<elevation id="54F78845FF9AFF89FC7AFDD3FC32FDC1" box="[908,965,518,545]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="50.0">50 m</elevation>
</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9AFF89FF4BFDFFFC7FFDA4" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,797]" box="[189,904,554,581]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FF4BFDFFFE4EFDA4" bold="true" box="[189,441,554,580]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
—Least Concern (LC) (Lansdown 2011).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF9AFF89FF4BFD9BFB6DFCFC" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FF4BFD9BFEFEFD88" bold="true" box="[189,265,590,616]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Notes:</emphasis>
—Within the region 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FE03FD9BFD18FD88" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1831" box="[501,751,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FE03FD9BFD18FD88" box="[501,751,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Callitriche platycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF9AFF89FC36FD9BFB82FD88" box="[960,1141,590,616]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
in CHR determined as this species by R. Mason, two of which represent material cultivated from the first gathering which was collected from North Island, Palmerston North, 
<date id="AB6449B6FF9AFF89FDF1FD43FD5FFD50" box="[519,680,662,688]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" value="1973-10">October 1973</date>
, 
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FD41FD43FC83FD50" box="[695,884,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Forde, M.B. s.n.</emphasis>
(CHR 279611, cultivated material CHR 279607 A, CHR 279607 B). Given the frequent problems with mis-identification of unfamiliar 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF9AFF89FB99FD6FFAB2FD34" box="[1135,1349,698,724]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF9AFF89FB99FD6FFB1FFD34" box="[1135,1256,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, even by specialists, this material needs to be confirmed by microscopic examination of pollen which is unique within the genus being tetrahedroid and appearing bluntly triangular in outline (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF9AFF89FCB2FCD7FBC4FCFD" author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[836,1075,770,797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="270" refId="ref33002" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2008) Water starworts of Europe. BSBI Handbook No. 11. Botanical Society of the British Isles, London, UK. 180 pp." type="book" year="2008">Lansdown 2008: 115</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF9AFF89FBC9FCD7FB7CFCFC" box="[1087,1163,770,796]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,225,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-31@4.[151,1436,190,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. antarctica, b—C. aucklandica, c—C. brachycarpa, d—C. brutia, e—C. capricorni, f—C. chathamensis, g—C. cyclocarpa i face on and ii end on, h—C. cycloptera, i—C. deflexa, j—C. fuliginea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577540/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="270">Fig. I1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
